# Copy to sandbox/secret.env (gitignored) and fill in. Never commit the real file.
#
# sandbox/run-isolated.sh sources this and injects the values into the container.
#
# hanbit uses a LOCAL SQLite DB inside /workspace — there is NO cloud DB and therefore
# NO cloud credentials to inject here. The only (optional) secret is a GitHub token so the
# isolated Claude can manage the repo (PR / issue / release / push) directly.

# --- GitHub (gh CLI) — OPTIONAL ---
# A fine-grained Personal Access Token lets the sandbox manage GitHub directly (PR / issue /
# release / push). The bootstrap runs `gh auth setup-git`, so `git push` over https uses it too.
#
# Generate: GitHub → Settings → Developer settings → Personal access tokens → Fine-grained tokens.
# ✅ STRONGLY prefer a FINE-GRAINED token scoped to ONLY the programgarden_hanbit repo — this caps
#    the blast radius to that one repo. Grant just the permissions you need (e.g. Contents: RW,
#    Pull requests: RW, Issues: RW). Use a short expiry and revoke when done — a skip-permissions
#    agent holds this token.
# (A classic `ghp_…` token also works but is account-wide; avoid unless you must.)
#
# Leave it blank/commented to run WITHOUT GitHub access (the sandbox still works for local dev).
# GH_TOKEN=github_pat_your_fine_grained_token_here
